text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia jonesii is a species of Acacia native to eastern Australia.
The spreading slender shrub typically grows to 0.4 to 4 metres (1 to 13 ft) in height. It has smooth brown to grey-green often mottled bark, terete branchlets and subsessile leaves that are 1 to 6.5 centimetres (0.4 to 2.6 in) long.
